{
  "texts": [
    "After the transformer blocks, a one-dimensional convolutional network and a fully-connected layer are added to decode the transformer output and form the final latent-space vector prediction.",
    "The architecture is illustrated in Fig. 9b.",
    "The LSTM model architecture includes four layers of LSTM elements, followed by a fully-connected layer of 128 neurons and a final output layer matching the latent-space size.",
    "The time-delay dimension for the LSTM is the same as transformer models.",
    "The KNF-model implementation is based in the code from Ref. 27."
  ]
}